  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth-linux-amd64-1.8.19-dae82f09`\r\nOS & Version: `Linux 4.9.0-6-amd64 #1 SMP Debian 4.9.88-1+deb9u1 (2018-05-07) x86_64 GNU/Linux`\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\ngeth list accounts well\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\ngeth list accounts when:\r\n* run as  `./geth --keystore \"/usr/local/eth/wallets\" --testnet console --rpc admin,eth,miner,personal,web3`\r\n* type `eth.accounts`\r\n\r\ngeth **DOES NOT** list accounts when:\r\n* run as  `./geth --testnet console --rpc admin,eth,miner,personal,web3 --keystore \"/usr/local/eth/wallets\"`\r\n* type `eth.accounts` i have `[]` output and geth points to *default keystore.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nrun as  `./geth --testnet console --rpc admin,eth,miner,personal,web3 --keystore \"/usr/local/eth/wallets\"` and type `eth.accounts`\r\n\r\n\r\n*it points to default keystore, because when i seen it, i created a new account via `geth.ipc` and i got a new address file in a default keystore.",
